<h1 align="center"><font color="#FF0000"><br>
About ASP.NET Web Matrix<br>
&nbsp;</font></h1>

<blockquote>
  <blockquote>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0px" align="left"><b>What is said about Web Matrix:
    </b>A tool for developing ASP.NET Web application <font color="#0000FF">
    watered-down version of Visual Studio</font> .Net that supports basic 
    ASP.Net coding for <font color="#0000FF">simpler Web applications</font>. It 
    was implemented 100% using C# and the .NET Framework. It is a 
    community-supported, easy-to-use <font color="#0000FF">WYSIWYG</font> 
    application development too.&nbsp; You can build applications using either 
    the <font color="#0000FF">Visual Basic or C# </font>programming languages
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0px" align="left"><b>Web Matrix History:&nbsp; </b>
    Back when <font color="#0000FF">ASP.NET</font> was in Beta, the ASP.NET team 
    decided that while <font color="#0000FF">Visual Studio .NET</font> was a 
    great overall development tool, it had three inhibiting
    <font color="#0000FF">drawbacks: its size, cost, and &quot;do everything&quot; nature</font>. 
    The Enterprise edition of Visual Studio .NET, for example,
    <font color="#0000FF">costs</font> several thousand dollars and uses 
    multiple CD.&nbsp; In order to combat these problems of Visual Studio .NET, 
    the ASP.NET team set out to create a new developer tool--one geared solely 
    for the <font color="#0000FF">ASP.NET developer</font>.&nbsp; The team 
    decided that this tool must be s<font color="#0000FF">mall, agile, great at 
    what it does, and inexpensive</font>.&nbsp; It was designed by people in the 
    ASP.NET team during their off hours -- <font color="#0000FF">after work</font> 
    and on the weekends.&nbsp; On<font color="#0000FF"> June 17th, 2002 </font>
    the ASP.NET team released their tool to the public.&nbsp; </p>





<body>





<p style="margin-bottom: 0px" align="left"><b>Requirements:</b> Size in its 
compressed downloadable form:<font color="#0000FF"> 1.2MB--fits on a floppy</font>--and 
consumes only <font color="#0000FF">2.5MB </font>of drive space.&nbsp; It 
requires the <font color="#0000FF">.NET Framework</font> and is supported on
<font color="#0000FF">Windows2000 and Windows XP. </font>&nbsp;Finally, it 
requires Microsoft <font color="#0000FF">Internet Explorer</font>--5.5 or later
</p>
    </blockquote>
  </blockquote>





</body>



